01:55:08,965 --> 01:55:10,956
I didn't give orders for a halt

1112
01:55:11,165 --> 01:55:12,564
We all need it

1113
01:55:16,485 --> 01:55:19,875
We're still five hours' fast march from the objective

1114
01:55:20,085 --> 01:55:21,359
Maybe six

1115
01:55:22,365 --> 01:55:23,480
Come on

1116
01:55:23,685 --> 01:55:26,119
If you keep walking  you'll bleed to death

1117
01:55:33,405 --> 01:55:36,317
You're going to leave me here   If you stop  we stop

1118
01:55:37,205 --> 01:55:39,719
You can't study the layout of the bridge after dark

1119
01:55:39,925 --> 01:55:41,961
You've got to get there before sundown

1120
01:55:42,165 --> 01:55:46,636
But  sir  when the job's done  who knows if we can return by this route

1121
01:55:46,885 --> 01:55:48,921
or whether we could find you if we did

1122
01:55:49,165 --> 01:55:52,555
If you were me  I wouldn't hesitate to leave you and you know that

1123
01:55:52,965 --> 01:55:54,159
He doesn't know  but I do

1124
01:55:54,405 --> 01:55:57,715
You'd leave your own mother here if the rules called for it

1125
01:55:58,405 --> 01:56:01,715
You'll go on without me  That's an order

1126
01:56:01,925 --> 01:56:04,120
You're in command now  Shears

1127
01:56:06,765 --> 01:56:08,517
I won't obey that order

1128
01:56:09,085 --> 01:56:10,564
Your heroics make me sick

1129
01:56:10,765 --> 01:56:13,438
You carry the stench of death like the plague

1130
01:56:13,685 --> 01:56:15,801
Explosives and L pills go well together

1131
01:56:16,165 --> 01:56:19,475
It's one thing or the other  Destroy a bridge or destroy yourself

1132
01:56:19,805 --> 01:56:21,443
This is just a game  this war

1133
01:56:21,685 --> 01:56:25,439
You and that Colonel Nicholson  You're crazy with courage  For what

1134
01:56:25,685 --> 01:56:28,518
How to die like a gentleman  how to die by the rules

1135
01:56:28,725 --> 01:56:32,320
when the only important thing is how to live like a human being

1136
01:56:36,165 --> 01:56:38,918
I'm not gonna leave you here to die  Warden

1137
01:56:40,205 --> 01:56:43,914
because I don't care about your bridge or about your rules

1138
01:56:44,365 --> 01:56:46,925
If we go on  we go on together

1139
01:56:49,725 --> 01:56:51,317
Good old Yai

1140
01:57:02,805 --> 01:57:03,920
All right

1141
01:57:14,165 --> 01:57:15,393
Come on

1142
01:58:02,885 --> 01:58:04,284
Let's get closer

1143
01:58:23,005 --> 01:58:25,121
Still sorry we brought you along

1144
01:58:26,725 --> 01:58:28,556
Feeling better   Yeah

1145
01:58:28,765 --> 01:58:30,915
You're in command again  you know

1146
01:58:31,125 --> 01:58:32,717
Thank you  major

1147
01:58:33,565 --> 01:58:38,355
I can't understand it  It's such a solid  well designed job

1148
01:58:40,965 --> 01:58:43,718
Not like the bridges the enemy usually throws together

1149
01:58:44,045 --> 01:58:45,239
Look

1150
01:58:47,005 --> 01:58:48,961
Those poor devils down there

1151
01:58:49,205 --> 01:58:52,880
Imagine being forced to build that in the condition they must be in

1152
01:58:53,965 --> 01:58:56,843
They've got a British officer working on his knees

1153
01:58:57,085 --> 01:58:59,076
The Japanese seem to be enjoying it too

1154
01:59:00,205 --> 01:59:02,924
If he knew we were here  it might boost his morale

1155
01:59:21,605 --> 01:59:24,845
If not for the train  we could set a time fuse and be miles away

1156
01:59:25,045 --> 01:59:27,764
Since we don't know what time it'll cross tomorrow

1157
01:59:28,005 --> 01:59:30,125
we'll have to do the job manually

1158
01:59:30,765 --> 01:59:33,404
We'll set the charges against the piles

1159
01:59:33,645 --> 01:59:37,001
about three feet underwater  I should think

1160
01:59:37,245 --> 01:59:40,442
and run the main wire downstream to the plunger

1161
01:59:41,645 --> 01:59:44,364
The problem is where to hide it

1162
01:59:49,325 --> 01:59:52,237
Our side of the river is obviously used by the Japanese

1163
01:59:52,565 --> 01:59:54,362
They'd spot it at once

1164
01:59:58,045 --> 02:00:01,082
Look  Do you see those fallen tree trunks

1165
02:00:01,325 --> 02:00:04,476
And the grey rock just below them on that little beach

1166
02:00:05,045 --> 02:00:08,401
Yes  sir  I see them   That's our key position

1167
02:00:09,405 --> 02:00:10,918
The wrong side of the river

1168
02:00:11,165 --> 02:00:14,601
but it's the only hiding place within feasible distance

1169
02:00:16,005 --> 02:00:17,996
As soon as the bridge goes up

1170
02:00:18,445 --> 02:00:21,198
whoever's there will have to swim back

1171
02:00:21,405 --> 02:00:23,316
It won't be a pleasant swim

1172
02:00:23,565 --> 02:00:25,999
Sir  I was the best swimmer in my course

1173
02:00:28,765 --> 02:00:31,040
It looks like your line of country  then

1174
02:00:31,245 --> 02:00:32,041
Thank you

1175
02:00:32,245 --> 02:00:35,920
Shears  pick a spot on our side of the bank where you can cover Joyce

1176
02:00:36,165 --> 02:00:38,963
Yai will be with you so you can occupy the Nips

1177
02:00:39,165 --> 02:00:41,235
if they make trouble for Joyce

1178
02:00:41,485 --> 02:00:43,840
On the theory that there's always one more thing

1179
02:00:44,085 --> 02:00:48,317
I'll set up the mortar here to create an additional diversion

1180
02:00:48,565 --> 02:00:51,796
Perhaps I might even take a few potshots at the train

1181
02:00:52,045 --> 02:00:53,239
All clear

1182
02:00:53,485 --> 02:00:56,636
Any questions  Right  you'll start as soon as it's dark

1183
02:00:56,845 --> 02:00:59,564
They're sure to have sentries on the bridge

1184
02:00:59,765 --> 02:01:03,440
so you'll have to float the stuff down from upriver

1185
02:01:03,685 --> 02:01:05,437
which means building a raft

1186
02:01:05,645 --> 02:01:06,634
Yai

1187
02:01:11,445 --> 02:01:13,800
Yai will take three women to help you

1188
02:01:14,045 --> 02:01:17,003
One will stay here with me  All right  get cracking

1189
02:01:22,045 --> 02:01:26,197
You know  if it wasn't for my ankle  I'd take Joyce's assignment

1190
02:01:26,805 --> 02:01:28,602
You think he'll be all right

1191
02:01:28,885 --> 02:01:31,194
I think so  Want me to handle it

1192
02:01:31,765 --> 02:01:34,598
I'd let you stay up here with the mortar if I could

1193
02:01:35,205 --> 02:01:36,399
I'm sorry

1194
02:01:37,085 --> 02:01:39,519
When it's over  I hope you get that medical discharge

1195
02:01:39,725 --> 02:01:41,602
and not the hard way

1196
02:01:41,805 --> 02:01:42,999
Thanks

1197
02:02:19,605 --> 02:02:20,594
Load

1198
02:03:23,725 --> 02:03:24,953
Beautiful

1199
02:03:25,685 --> 02:03:27,277
Yes  beautiful

1200
02:03:27,565 --> 02:03:29,283
A first rate job

1201
02:03:29,725 --> 02:03:32,080
I had no idea it would turn out so well

1202
02:03:37,245 --> 02:03:39,475
Yes  a beautiful creation

1203
02:03:40,645 --> 02:03:42,078
I've been thinking

1204
02:03:43,045 --> 02:03:47,482
Tomorrow it will be 28 years to the day that I've been in the service

1205
02:03:47,765 --> 02:03:50,279
Twenty eight years in peace and war

1206
02:03:51,525 --> 02:03:55,074
I haven't been at home more than ten months in all that time

1207
02:03:55,645 --> 02:03:57,875
Still  it's been a good life

1208
02:03:59,165 --> 02:04:01,201
I love India

1209
02:04:02,725 --> 02:04:04,875
I wouldn't have had it any other way

1210
02:04:06,485 --> 02:04:08,123
But there are times

1211
02:04:09,725 --> 02:04:13,877
Suddenly you realize you are nearer the end than the beginning

1212
02:04:14,845 --> 02:04:16,324
And you wonder

1213
02:04:17,925 --> 02:04:19,881
You ask yourself

1214
02:04:21,165 --> 02:04:24,282
what the sum total of your life represents

1215
02:04:25,045 --> 02:04:28,481
what difference your being there at any time made to anything

1216
02:04:28,965 --> 02:04:31,479
or if it made any difference at all  really

1217
02:04:33,045 --> 02:04:36,276
Particularly in comparison with other men's careers

1218
02:04:36,925 --> 02:04:39,314
I don't know if that kind of thinking's healthy

1219
02:04:39,885 --> 02:04:43,514
but I must admit I've had some thoughts on those lines

1220
02:04:43,765 --> 02:04:45,676
from time to time

1221
02:04:48,645 --> 02:04:50,283
But tonight

1222
02:04:51,685 --> 02:04:52,674
Tonight

1223
02:04:56,285 --> 02:04:57,684
Blast

1224
02:05:04,325 --> 02:05:05,724
I must be off

1225
02:05:08,445 --> 02:05:11,676
The men are preparing some sort of entertainment

1226
02:05:56,645 --> 02:05:57,873
Lovely

1227
02:08:01,525 --> 02:08:04,676
If you were the only

1228
02:08:04,885 --> 02:08:07,524
Girl in the world

1229
02:08:07,725 --> 02:08:12,640
And you were the only boy

1230
02:08:13,045 --> 02:08:15,320
Nothing else would matter

1231
02:08:15,525 --> 02:08:18,483
In the world today

1232
02:08:18,965 --> 02:08:20,921
We could go on loving

1233
02:08:21,125 --> 02:08:24,197
In the same old way

1234
02:08:24,765 --> 02:08:29,680
A Garden of Eden just made for two

1235
02:12:52,365 --> 02:12:54,117
I'm sure I speak for all of us

1236
02:12:54,325 --> 02:12:57,283
when I say this has been a most enjoyable evening

1237
02:12:58,965 --> 02:13:03,880
Most of you move on tomorrow to a new camp and new construction

1238
02:13:04,325 --> 02:13:08,477
It's a pity you won't see the first practical use of this bridge

1239
02:13:08,725 --> 02:13:11,285
You'll be glad to know that the completion

1240
02:13:11,525 --> 02:13:13,641
of this link in the railway

1241
02:13:13,845 --> 02:13:17,076
will enable us to transport the sick and disabled

1242
02:13:17,325 --> 02:13:20,283
to the new camp by train

1243
02:13:21,845 --> 02:13:24,678
Colonel Saito has kindly permitted me to stay behind

1244
02:13:24,885 --> 02:13:27,115
with Major Clipton and the sick men

1245
02:13:27,365 --> 02:13:30,721
and we'll rejoin you in a few days' time

1246
02:13:32,685 --> 02:13:35,685
Now that your work here is finished

1247
02:13:35,925 --> 02:13:39,804
I suppose many of you feel somewhat let down

1248
02:13:40,565 --> 02:13:42,476
That's quite understandable

1249
02:13:42,765 --> 02:13:45,279
It's a very natural reaction

1250
02:13:47,565 --> 02:13:50,682
But one day  in a week  a month  a year

1251
02:13:50,885 --> 02:13:54,560
on that day when  God willing  we all return to our homes again

1252
02:13:55,245 --> 02:14:00,160
you're going to feel very proud of what you've achieved here

1253
02:14:00,485 --> 02:14:03,079
in the face of great adversity

1254
02:14:04,245 --> 02:14:06,281
What you have done should be

1255
02:14:07,125 --> 02:14:08,877
and I think will be

1256
02:14:09,245 --> 02:14:13,682
an example to all our countrymen  soldier and civilian alike

1257
02:14:14,845 --> 02:14:17,279
You have survived with honor

1258
02:14:18,165 --> 02:14:19,883
That  and more

1259
02:14:21,445 --> 02:14:23,481
Here in the wilderness

1260
02:14:23,765 --> 02:14:27,075
you have turned defeat into victory

1261
02:14:29,725 --> 02:14:31,681
I congratulate you

1262
02:14:32,205 --> 02:14:33,194
Well done

1263
02:14:38,365 --> 02:14:39,593
To the king

1264
02:17:15,325 --> 02:17:16,724
You're in business

1265
02:17:16,925 --> 02:17:20,884
Now  you got everything  Stem  ammunition  pack  canteen  knife

1266
02:17:22,485 --> 02:17:24,680
I'll be directly across the river

1267
02:17:26,085 --> 02:17:28,883
The professor says there's always one more thing to do

1268
02:17:29,565 --> 02:17:31,681
I can't think of what it could be

1269
02:17:33,045 --> 02:17:35,479
Except to wish you a long and happy life

1270
02:17:35,885 --> 02:17:36,920
Thank you

